{
  "texts": [
    "In the context of knowledge distillation of LLM T, we address the problem of efficiently annotating an unlabeled question set U.",
    "This involves strategically selecting a subset Q from U, where Q ⊂ U and |Q| < |U|.",
    "Our study's primary goal is to enhance the performance of a smaller model S through fine-tuning with a training dataset D = {(q i, âi, ri)} |Q|, where the LLM annotates an answer â and a corresponding explanation r for each question q ∈ Q, forming D. The objective is to achieve a performance with S that is comparable to that of T, while minimizing the size of the annotated dataset Q.",
    "This approach aims to maximize the efficiency of the small model and minimize the amount of annotated data required from the LLM.",
    "In this section, we first present the overview of our proposed Explanation-Guided LLMs Active Distillation framework."
  ]
}